The paper deals with consensus in dynamic networks, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of topology and distance functions to analyze the space of infinite executions suggests a connection to topology and geometry (cs.SI), as well as information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses fairness and connectivity, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and network science (cs.NI), respectively.
